senses
  entry
    definition "the activity of protecting someone or something"
    examples ("the witnesses demanded police protection")
    id oewn-00819341-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "a covering that is intend to protect from damage or injury"
    examples ("they had no protection from the fallout" "wax provided protection for the floors")
    id oewn-04020673-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms ("protective covering" "protective cover")
  entry
    definition "defense against financial failure; financial independence"
    examples ("his pension gave him security in his old age" "insurance provided protection against loss of wages due to illness")
    id oewn-13365086-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (security)
  entry
    definition "the condition of being protected"
    examples ("they were huddled together for protection" "he enjoyed a sense of peace and protection in his new home")
    id oewn-14563562-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (shelter)
  entry
    definition "kindly endorsement and guidance"
    examples ("the tournament was held under the auspices of the city council")
    id oewn-01217353-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (auspices aegis)
  entry
    definition "the imposition of duties or quotas on imports in order to protect domestic industry against foreign competition"
    examples ("he made trade protection a plank in the party platform")
    id oewn-01130195-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms ("trade protection")
  entry
    definition "payment extorted by gangsters on threat of violence"
    examples ("every store in the neighborhood had to pay him protection")
    id oewn-00786409-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (tribute)
